First, we need to understand what it means for a set to have infinite VCₙ dimension. A set C has VCₙ dimension infinite if there exists a function f : ℕ → Fin (n + 2) → ℝ such that for any subset s of ℕ, there exists a point y ∈ ℝ^(n+2) such that f(s) + y ∈ C if and only if s is in the subset. 

